abstract: >
  Digital Pedon is a dictionary-first, stdlib-only Python framework implementing
  a three-layer digital twin for soil profiles. It ingests sensor and remote
  sensing data through a declarative BYOD manifest, runs physics-based solvers
  (Van Genuchten, Darcy-Buckingham, De Vries heat equation, Q10 respiration),
  fires configurable threshold alarms, and stores a time-series history — all
  operating on plain Python dicts with no external dependencies. The framework
  is GLOSIS-compliant and exports JSON-LD for submission to FAO, ESDAC, and
  any OGC-compliant soil information system. An LLM-readable JSON-LD context
  manifest and OpenAI-compatible tool schema enable LLM agents to call
  Digital Pedon methods as native tools.
